<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1957-11-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1957-11-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="843" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d843">
                        <head>843. Telegram 182 to Prague<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d843fn1">Source: Department of State, Central Files, 611.93/11–2157.
                                Confidential; Priority; Limit Distribution. Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_CRN_1">Clough</persName>; cleared by Howe (S/S),
                                Henderson (O), and Elbrick (EUR). The time of transmission is
                                illegible.</note></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1957-11-21">November 21,
                                1957</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <pb facs="d843-1" n="1" type="facsimile" xml:id="d843-1"/>
                        <p>182. For Ambassador Only. Your tel 297.</p>
                        <p>We agree you should go ahead with December 12 meeting.</p>
                        <p>Would like your comment on following alternative methods continuing talks
                            under consideration here: 1) Beam meet with <persName corresp="#p_WP_1">Wang</persName> in Warsaw, 2) Rankin commute Geneva from Belgrade
                            following assignment there, 3) talks be continued at lower level and
                            conducted by <persName corresp="#p_MEW_1">Martin</persName> commuting to
                            Geneva.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_DJF_1"><hi rend="strong">Dulles</hi></persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>